public class PatternMatch
extends java.util.ArrayList<VariableAssignment>

PatternMatch A pattern match is a mapping of constants onto variables. It is a list of variable assignments. Given a before graph, an input graph and their pattern match, you can eliminate the variables in before. One pair of input and before can have multiple pattern matches. To create a pattern match you need a before and an input. Creation of objects of this class is done in Rule.java.
